      .span8#faq
        %h2
          What is CareContent?
        %p
          It's a robust content service that allows hospitals and health systems to update web site pages, feed e-newsletters and finally link to something
          worthwhile on social media sites. CareContent licenses feature stories, quizzes, current news articles, photos and illustrations from a 
          growing repository of web content. Stop dreading the next website update or e-newsletter deadline. Now you can get excited about updating your web
          vehicles with content patients will love reading.
        %h2
          How does the service work?
        %ol
          %li
            Log in.
          %li
            Select the content you want for your website or e-newsletter. The content you select is guaranteed to be exclusive within your primary and secondary
            service area for one full year.
          %li
            Edit the content to your heart's delight. Use the "quick quote" prompts to add insights from your hospital or health system's clinicians and leaders
            (or skip them, no pressure). Include information about your organization's programs and services, along with a photo or two. (We strongly recommend
            giving quoted sources the opportunity to review the content before publishing).
          %li
            Post it on your landing page or insert it in your e-newsletter.
          %li
            Don't forget to mention the new content on your social media vehicles. Tweet one of the added or post it as your organization's new Facebook status update.
        %h2
          Where do I sign up?
        %p
          Try it free for 30-days. After that, CareContent is available for a tiered monthly subscription, based on how munch content is needed each month.
